02 - Domain Deployment
Overview
This phase covers the installation of Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS) and the promotion of DC01 to a Domain Controller for the corp.local domain.

Steps Performed
1. Install AD DS Role

Opened Server Manager and added the Active Directory Domain Services role via the Add Roles and Features Wizard
Also installed DNS Server as part of the role installation (required for AD DS)

How to install the role:
Server Manager → Manage → Add Roles and Features →
Role-based installation → Select "Active Directory Domain Services" → Install

2. Post-Deployment Configuration

After role installation, a notification appeared in Server Manager:
"Configuration required for Active Directory Domain Services at DC01"
Clicked "Promote this server to a domain controller" to launch the AD DS Configuration Wizard


3. AD DS Configuration Wizard
Deployment Configuration:

Selected: Add a new forest
Root domain name: corp.local

Domain Controller Options:

Forest functional level: Windows Server 2016
Domain functional level: Windows Server 2016
DNS Server: ✅ Enabled
Global Catalog (GC): ✅ Enabled
Set Directory Services Restore Mode (DSRM) password

DNS Options:

A delegation warning appeared — this is expected behavior in an isolated lab environment with no parent DNS zone. No action required.

Additional Options:

NetBIOS domain name: CORP (auto-populated)

Paths (defaults accepted):
ComponentDefault PathAD DS DatabaseC:\Windows\NTDSLog filesC:\Windows\NTDSSYSVOLC:\Windows\SYSVOL
Installation:

Reviewed configuration summary
Clicked Install
Server automatically restarted after promotion


DNS Warning Explanation
During installation, two warnings appeared:

"A delegation for this DNS server cannot be created because the authoritative parent zone cannot be found."


"Windows Server 2022 domain controllers have a default for the security setting named 'Allow cryptography algorithms compatible with Windows NT 4.0'..."

Both are expected and safe to ignore in a standalone lab environment. They are not errors and do not affect functionality.

Result
At the end of this phase:

✅ AD DS role installed on DC01
✅ DC01 promoted to Domain Controller
✅ New forest created: corp.local
✅ DNS Server running and integrated with AD
✅ Server restarted and logged in as CORP\Administrator


